headline: Target, Home Depot, and Zoom: Stocks to watch this week
summary: Last week, surprise news of a temporary and tentative U.S.-China trade deal set stocks roaring from Monday on, though optimism cooled by Friday as skepticism mounted and commentators focused on yet another 90-day pause. The S&P 500 ended the week on a positive note, while the Nasdaq spiked midweek on Nvidia’s (NVDA) Saudi Arabian opportunity — only to finish flat. The Dow, weighed down by UnitedHealthcare’s (UNH) ongoing crisis, still managed to close in the green.
